{"lemma":"شارِعَيْ","slug":"شارِعَيْ","root":"ش.ر.ع","root_slug":"ش-ر-ع","root_link":"/words/roots/ش-ر-ع","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n22150"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B4%D8%A7%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%8A%D9%92"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"street"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"legislator"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From the root ش ر ع (š r ʕ). Has the form of an active participle but the corresponding verb شَرَعَ (šaraʕa, “to have an outlet into the street”) may rather be derived from the noun; other meanings of the verb don't fit."},"ipa":["/ʃaː.riʕ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n22150","headword_ar":"شَارِعٌ","root":"$rE","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Entering into water"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to drink"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aEN","text_ar":"شُرَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$uruwEN","text_ar":"شُرُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (KL:) these pls. are applied in this sense to camels. (S, K.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Entering"},{"kind":"text","text":"into an affair ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiY A^amorK","text_ar":"فِى اَمْرٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (Az, TA.) See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$araEN","text_ar":"شَرَعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-  And sing. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aEN","text_ar":"شُرَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the phrase"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HiytaAnN $ur~aEN","text_ar":"حِيتَانٌ شُرَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) which means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Fishes lowering their heads to drink:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Leylà, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"raising their heads:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"directing themselves,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"repairing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriEaAtN","text_ar":"شَارِعَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from the deep water to the bank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"side:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HytAn $uruwEN","text_ar":"حيتان شُرُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aEFA","text_ar":"شُرَّعًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur vii. 163, referring to fish, means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearing upon the surface of the water."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Bd, Jel. *) ―         -b4-  Also, applied to a place of alighting, or an abode, ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"manozilN","text_ar":"مَنْزِلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Situate upon a road that is a thoroughfare:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriEapN","text_ar":"شَارِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a house ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN","text_ar":"دَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") signifies the same; (K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having its door"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opening"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon such a road;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near to the road and to the people"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"passengers"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Mgh, * TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwrN $aAriEapN","text_ar":"دُورٌ شَارِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"houses having their doors opening into the streets:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwrN $awaAriEu","text_ar":"دُورٌ شَوَارِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as expl. by IDrd,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"houses upon one open road."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) It is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaAnati AlA^abowaAbu","text_ar":"كَانَتِ الاَبْوَابُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriEapF A_ilaY Almasojidi","text_ar":"شَارِعَةً اـِلَى المَسْجِدِ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The doors were opening towards the mosque."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  And Anything"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"near"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) to a thing, or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"overlooking"},{"kind":"text","text":"it: whence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriEapN","text_ar":"شَارِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a house ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN","text_ar":"دَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":") near to the road and to the people, as expl. above. (TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nujuwmN $awaAriEu","text_ar":"نُجُومٌ شَوَارِعُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Stars near to setting."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K.) ―         -b6-  [Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Pointing directly"},{"kind":"text","text":"towards a person; applied to a spear.] One says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rimaAHN $aAriEapN","text_ar":"رِمَاحٌ شَارِعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awaAriEu","text_ar":"شَوَارِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ur~aEN","text_ar":"شُرَّعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as in some of the copies of the S (TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Spears pointing directly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rimaAHN ma$oruwEapN","text_ar":"رِمَاحٌ مَشْرُوعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mu$oraEapN","text_ar":"مُشْرَعَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spears directed."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b7-  Also [used as a subst.]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A main road:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) or it signifies, (Mgh, TA,) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TariyqN $aAriEN","text_ar":"طَرِيقٌ شَارِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a road,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way, into which people enter"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yasolukuhu Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"يَسْلُكُهُ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Msb, or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ya$oraEu fiyhi Aln~aAsu","text_ar":"يَشْرَعُ فِيهِ النَّاسُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", Mgh, TA)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in common,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in general;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA;) by a tropical attribution; (Mgh;) [i. e.]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriEN","text_ar":"شَارِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in this case has the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oruwEN","text_ar":"مَشْرُوعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ma$oruwEN fiyhi","text_ar":"مَشْرُوعٌ فِيهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (Msb;) or as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"*uw $aroEK mina Alxaloqi","text_ar":"ذُو شَرْعٍ مِنَ الخَلْقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having an entering of people"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (TA:) or it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a manifest, plain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conspicuous, road"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"way:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, TA:) [in the present day,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$aAriEN","text_ar":"شَارِعٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"commonly signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any great street that is a thoroughfare:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the pl. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$awAriEu","text_ar":"شَوارِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aAriEu","text_ar":"الشَّارِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The learned man who practises what he knows and instructs others:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA:) or so"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~aAriEu Alr~ab~aAniY~u","text_ar":"الشَّارِعُ الرَّبَّانِىُّ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O.) And hence it is applied to designate the Prophet: [or as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The legislator:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the announcer of the law:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or because he made manifest and plain the religion, or religious law of God. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["KL","TA","K","S","O","Mgh","Msb"]}]}}